  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your<strong> carrot[s] </strong>into batons</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your<strong> parsnip[s] </strong>into batons</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677858186657-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677858186657-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677858186657-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677858186657-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1677858186657-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> carrot batons</strong>, <strong>parsnip batons </strong>and <strong>onion petals</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>ground coriander</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20 min or until the vegetables are tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677858198350-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677858198350-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677858198350-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677858198350-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1677858198350-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a medium-sized pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>flaked</strong> <strong>almonds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden then transfer to a chopping board, reserve the pot</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677858213466-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677858213466-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677858213466-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677858213466-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1677858213466-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the reserved pot with<strong> cold water </strong>and add your<strong> spelt</strong> with plenty of <strong>boiling water</strong>, then add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 20 min or until tender (it will still have a slight bite once cooked)</p><p>Once cooked, drain and rinse the <strong>cooked spelt</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until the spelt has cooled slightly and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1677858221803-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1677858221803-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1677858221803-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1677858221803-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1677858221803-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Zest half your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter) and cut in half (save the zest for garnish!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1677858232470-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1677858232470-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1677858232470-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1677858232470-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1677858232470-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables are tender, remove the tray[s] from the oven and top with your<strong> honey</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up then return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 5 min or until caramelised<strong> </strong>–<strong> </strong>these are your <strong>honey roasted roots</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1677858240902-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1677858240902-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1677858240902-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1677858240902-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1677858240902-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>zested</strong> <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in a bowl with your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>lemon mustard dressing</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>cooked spelt</strong>,<strong> salad</strong>, <strong>diced apricots</strong>, most<strong> </strong>of<strong> </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and most of your <strong>toasted almonds </strong>(save some for garnish!) to the bowl with the dressing</p><p>Mix everything together until fully combined – these are your <strong>spelt grains</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1677858249725-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1677858249725-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1677858249725-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1677858249725-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1677858249725-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Serve the<strong> spelt grains</strong> topped with the <strong>honey roasted roots</strong> and crumble over your <strong>goats’ cheese</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>toasted almonds</strong>, <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and <strong>lemon zest</strong> and garnish with a<strong> lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
